                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d251">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1069a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-19T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department is impressed that the basis of permanent improvement in Dominican
                    affairs depends upon the Constitutional Convention and Congress adopting its
                    recent suggestions for reforms.</p>
                <p>Personally interview President Bordas privately. Ascertain if he considers
                    elimination of Arias and Vidal wall enable Convention and Congress to complete
                    suggested reforms, and whether the position of Delegate in the Cibao, held by
                    Arias, is constitutional, how many soldiers he has, whether his salary and
                    sustenance and salaries of his soldiers are provided by the budget and paid by
                    the Government, and, finally, how President Bordas plans to eliminate Arias and
                    whether a serious revolution might not result in case Arias is dismissed and
                    proclaimed an outlaw, as suggested in your February 12, 9 a.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
